American International Group Inc.,
the insurer that repaid a U.S. bailout last year, said Joseph J. Trotti has rejoined the company as chief executive officer of
the aerospace division.  Trotti, who will be based in London, was executive vice
president of the business before leaving in 2002, and worked
most recently for Willis Group Holdings Plc, New York-based AIG
said today in a statement distributed by Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
